title: For Sale:  Reduced: AK47 Saiga 7.62x39 converted with extras
postcontent:
I've decided to sell my fully converted Saiga 7.62x39 AK-47.  Bought it brand new prior to the ban on import, had it converted using Carolina Shooters Supply parts along with some extras below.  

Fully converted minus the forend, I actually like the extended Saiga style but I have a black polymer standard AK forend if you choose you can swap it with a clamp on style front retainer to go full original AK look.
Ultimak gas tube (holds zero perfectly, had a micro dot on it)
Threaded barrel in 14x1 LH with CNC Warrior brake/compensator
Magpul MVG vertical grip, cut down for use as hand stop
Custom extended safety
Custom sling mounts with multiple configurations
Recent soda blast strip, Gunkote black on all metal parts and flat OD green on the furniture.
Includes 4 Chicom steel magazines painted the same OD green
Box of random AK goodies, what you see is what you get

Let's do a quick value analysis here...
Saiga IZ132 7.62x39 rifle - $600 (shipped/FFL fee) or more if bought locally
Conversion kit - $180 (Carolina Shooters Supply, Conversion kit #6) **This is assuming you're able to do the conversion yourself not not pay a gunsmith, that would be another $150-$200**
Install bullet guide $50 (Gunsmith fee)
Thread the muzzle $90 (Gunsmith fee)
Ultimak $100
Extended Safety $65 (Krebs is the best I can compare)
Sling mounts $50 (if bought and not made)
Muzzle brake $30 (CNC Warrior, Knurled Compensator)
Vertical grip $15 (Magpul MVG)
Chinese surplus steel mags $25/ea = $100
You're looking over $1200 to recreate this rifle. Absolutely worth every penny as it's the best AK you can get. This is why I am NOT entertaining offers of $800 or less...sorry. 

I'm asking $900. Serious buyers only please. No trades.
